  "title": "Quantity Surveyor (HDB/ Condominium Projects)",
  "description": "<p>Our esteemed client in the <strong>Construction industry</strong> is seeking a <strong>Quantity Surveyor </strong>to join their dynamic team:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Employment Type: </strong>Permanent</li>\n  <li><strong>Position:</strong> Quantity Surveyor / Tender Executive</li>\n  <li><strong>Location:</strong> Central (Nearest MRT: Mattar)</li>\n  <li><strong>Working Hours:</strong> 5 days, Office Hours</li>\n  <li><strong>Salary Package:</strong> Up to $6,800 + Bonus</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Manage the collection and analysis of tender documents, including mastering project drawings and specifications.</li>\n  <li>Perform the bidding quantity calculation process and provide guidance to junior staff members.</li>\n  <li>Prepare accurate bills of quantities and carry out detailed quantity take-offs for projects.</li>\n  <li>Source and liaise with suppliers and subcontractors to collate and compare pricing.</li>\n  <li>Manage the subcontractor solicitation process, organizing negotiations to secure competitive prices.</li>\n  <li>Consolidate and check bidding calculations and documentation from team members.</li>\n  <li>Develop and maintain comprehensive unit price tables for tender submissions.</li>\n  <li>Compile the final bidding quotation list and submit it to department management for review.</li>\n  <li>Oversee the archiving of all tender offer data and documentation.</li>\n  <li>Perform risk analysis, value management, and cost control activities during the tender phase.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>At least a Diploma in Quantity Surveying or related discipline.</li>\n  <li>Minimum 3 years of experience working in the construction industry, with experience in handling HDB or Condominiums projects.</li>\n  <li>Strong knowledge of contract negotiation and administration.</li>\n  <li>Experience in a pre-contract role, or a mixture of both pre and post-contract functions.</li>\n  <li>Familiar with Glodon software.</li>\n  <li>Able to work in a fast paced environment and under tight deadlines.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Ready to apply? Here’s how:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Click the APPLY button, or</li>\n  <li>Email your resume (in MS Word or PDF format) to <a href=\"mailto:adelin@intuitrecruitment.com\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>adelin@intuitrecruitment.com</strong>.</a> Include the job title in your email subject line for prompt processing.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em><strong>Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</strong></em></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>By submitting your application, you consent to the collection and use of your personal data under Personal Data Protection Act (PDPA).</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Adelin Chong | EA Personnel Reg No.: R1875641</p>\n<p>Intuit Recruitment Pte Ltd | EA License No.: 25C2793</p>",
